To anyone looking for that gentle and convincing encouragement in your ear, this is an excellent app. I loved and appreciated being able to load up high energy pace setting music at the same time, as having Jo Whileys' (my choice for instructor) positivity exuding confidence. The incremental steps to get you running non stop for 30 minutes is astonishing, considering I never imagined I could run at the start, I am now looking ahead and now training for a 10k race!

This is an excellent programme that gets you running and in much better shape. I have completed the full programme twice now. The biggest flaw is that there is no follow-on plan. So after couch-to-5k I did 5k-to-couch! Update: reducing to 2 stars because regrettably the excellent trainer Michael Johnson is being removed. Why??

Just finished my final run today! I have always hated running but this app has changed the way i approach runs. I'm going to be continuing. For anyone just starting I would say wk 4 is a step up from the first 3 weeks but you can do it. And you won't stop from there! Excellent guidance

Really enjoyed using this App

Great

Great motivation!

Great way to get into running again and though the longer periods of running seem daunting you do find yourself doing it. The one thing I would like to see fixed is the voice overs. It's very obvious that they recorded a run one session for each week and that's it. So you are completing run 3 and it's still telling you that you need to do 2 more runs that week, or you start week 2 and on run 3 it's still reminding you to complete the 3 runs in week 1.

This prescriptive approach took me from being a non-runner to running 5k three times a week nonstop. If you don't feel ready to step up then no pressure, stay at the same level until you feel read to progress.

A very clear, simple and easy to use app that does what it says. Follow the training and you will be running 5k within 9 weeks. Works well with Spotify and Play music apps so you can listen to podcasts or music as you run whilst still being able to hear your coach's instructions. My only gripe would be the very limited number of coach's available. Last time I checked there were 4 to choose from...maybe not someone for everyone. Apart from that, it is a great app.
User friendly and very supportive and encouraging.

Great app and does what it says on the tin. If you do have a training programme already going its difficult to combine both, but practice runs are important as they set you up for final distance. Dont skip your runs!
